# Formatted by publCIF 
data_P21-c_a_FINAL

# start Validation Reply Form
_vrf_REFNR01_P21-c_a_FINAL
;
PROBLEM: Ratio of reflections to parameters is < 6 for a
RESPONSE: The highly symmetric, perfluorinated aluminumalkoxide anions are 
known to be heavily disordered at 100 K (very small rotational barriers of the 
-C(CF3)3 moieties). As a result, the isotropic displacement parameters became 
larger, leading to weaker scattering power and ultimately to lower 
resolutions (i.e. the scattering power inverseley correlates to the exponent
of the square of the isotropic displacement parameter).
;
_vrf_THETM01_P21-c_a_FINAL
;
PROBLEM: The value of sine(theta_max)/wavelength is less than 0.550
RESPONSE: Due to the heavy disorder of the highly symmetric, perfluorinated 
aluminumalkoxide anions the scattering power and ultimately the theta_max 
values are very little.
;
_vrf_PLAT088_P21-c_a_FINAL
;
PROBLEM: Poor Data / Parameter Ratio ....................       5.93 Note  
RESPONSE: The heavy disorder of the highly symmetric, perfluorinated 
aluminumalkoxide anions was treated appropriately using a disorder model. This
strategy led to an increase in parameters and expectedly to a drop in the 
data/parameter ration. From a  chemical point of view however, the bond lenghts 
of the aluminumalkoxide anions were restrained to be equal, thus yielding a 
very stable model with very little residual density.
;
_vrf_PLAT018_P21-c_a_FINAL
;
PROBLEM: _diffrn_measured_fraction_theta_max .NE. _full           ! Check
RESPONSE: This alert is also a result of the weak scattering power of the
highly disordered aluminumalkoxide anions (see above).
;
_vrf_PLAT342_P21-c_a_FINAL
;
PROBLEM: Low Bond Precision on  C-C Bonds ...............     0.0208 Ang.  
RESPONSE: This alert is also a result of the weak scattering power of the
highly disordered aluminumalkoxide anions (see above). While the atom 
assignment and connectivities are unambiguously correctly described, 
the non-optimal, but reasonable data makes it difficult to address bond 
distances at a high level of accuracy.
;
# end Validation Reply Form

